title: Sidewall, 1850–70
inscribed: Written in script on verso in graphite: "Capt. Farless/ 120 Derby Street/ Aug. 8th 1862/ Chambers" and "Salem". Printed in selvedge: "1346".
creditline: Gift of The Museum at The Fashion Institute of Technology
description: Diamond trellis design. Trellis pattern is gray band with vining floral. Insedt panels containing floral bouquet. Printed in brown, green and gray on off-white ground. c. 1850, from Capt. Farlen House, Salem. Printed in selvedge: "1346".

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, 1850–70.
1850–70. Machine-printed on machine-made paper. Gift of The Museum at The Fashion Institute of Technology. 1998-75-209.
